HEADWORD: Incontiguous
<hw>In`con*tig"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incontiguus</ets> that can not be touched. See <er>In-</er> not,
and <er>Contiguous</er>.]</ety> <def>Not contiguous; not adjoining or in
contact; separate.</def> <au>Boyle.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>In`con*tig"u*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms></p>

